普通常用词，含义广泛，指陌生新奇、奇怪、奇怪或不自然的人或物。
指一种无法解释的怪诞，强调事物的奇特和不可思议。

通常指异常或奇特，暗含不同于一般。
指古色古香，会人感到既奇怪又有趣。

list.abstract: strange（英 [streɪndʒ]，美 [streɪndʒ]），是英文单词，作形容词为不平常的；奇特的；奇怪的；不可思议的等。短语搭配有strange behavior（古怪的行为）。例句为“His comment struck me as strange.（他的评论使我感到奇怪。）” 该单词的名词形式为stranger、strangeness，副词形式为strangely，近义词为unknown、lay、queerly、anticly，反义词为familiar、native。
strange是一个英语单词，可以用作形容词和副词，可以翻译为陌生的、生疏的，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: And there are strange devices on their boat!
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且他们的船上有各式各样奇怪的道具！

yingyinNormal.en: Strange, because it's quite an adult taste actually.
yingyinNormal.zh: 奇怪的是，吃起来是大人的味道。

yingyinNormal.en: What strange noises. I wonder if we should check upstairs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是什么奇怪的声音。不知道我们该不该上楼去确认一下。

yingyinNormal.en: There's strange magic here!
yingyinNormal.zh: 这有一种奇怪的魔法！

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa isn't under the bed. What was that strange noise? Peppa isn't behind the curtain. There is that strange noise again!
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩琪也没有藏在床底下。刚才那是什么声音？佩琪也没有藏在窗帘后面。乔治又听到那个奇怪的声音。

yingyinNormal.en: What? With a man? What? What's so strange about me having a date?
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？跟男人？怎么？我有约会有什么奇怪的？

yingyinNormal.en: A whole world and exchange for a statue. Gods are strange creatures.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一尊雕像换来一整个世界，神真是奇怪的生物。

yingyinNormal.en: What was that strange noise? Peppa, George! Quick, come inside the house!
yingyinNormal.zh: 那个奇怪的噪音是什么？佩佩，乔治！快，快进房子里来！

yingyinNormal.en: What was that strange noise? Peppa, George. Quick, come inside the house.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这奇怪的声音是什么呀？佩琪，乔治，快一点，快回到屋子里来。

yingyinNormal.en: I know it's a strange concept. But I don't like when categories get confused.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我知道这是个奇怪的概念，但我不喜欢概念混淆。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't want your money, bowhead. Then why do you pick on me? How can I not? You're a strange duck, Matthews.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不想要你的钱，大脑门。那你为什么要找我茬？ 我怎么能不这样呢？你是一个奇怪的乖乖女，马修斯。

yingyinNormal.en: That's the long shot. There's a Plan A and a Plan B. Did you notice anything strange about the launch chamber?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那才是真正的赌注，有个A计划 ，还有个B计划，你发现发射室有什么奇怪的地方吗？

yingyinNormal.en: How strange. No loud noises? That's right. How many times around the house was it, Mummy pig? Three time? Fifty times.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好奇怪的办法！你需要制造噪音吗？完全不需要。我们要围着屋子转几圈，猪妈妈？是三圈吗？是五十圈。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm a strange duck. Quack! Hey. This looks better than usual. You're sure this is a C+? It might be a B-. I told you never a B-.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是一只奇怪的鸭子，嘎嘎！嘿，这比平常的看起来要好。你确定这是C+？可能会是B-。我说过绝对不能拿B-。

yingyinNormal.en: A black hole is a strange beast. If this were a black hole, then instead of a rubber surface it would have a surface that is made of absolutely nothing except warped space and time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黑洞就是一个奇怪的野兽。如果这是个黑洞，那么就不会是个胶面，它会有一个除了弯曲的时空什么也没有的表面。

yingyinNormal.en: Internet, a part of the century in the past 20 years, was pretty successful, but one thing that is very strange (is) that I found that very few Internet companies can survive peacefully and healthily for more than 3 years.
yingyinNormal.zh: 过去20年，互联网非常成功，是我发现一个非常奇怪的事情，很少有互联网公司能健康、平静地活过3年。

yingyinNormal.en: Good-bye, you poor, strange little man.
yingyinNormal.zh: 再见，你这个可怜的怪人。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a strange thing seeing your boy become a man.
yingyinNormal.zh: 说来挺奇妙的，看见儿子长大成人了。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Night at the Museum: Secret of the Tomb》

yingyinNormal.en: That's strange. We don't have a ladder in our garden.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是奇怪。我们花园里没有梯子。

yingyinNormal.en: Have you seen anything strange? Is he shitting me? Visions.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有没有看到什么异象?你在开玩笑吗?幻象。

word_usage.usage:
be strange to me的含义是“我不认识…”“...对我很陌生”，而非“…不认识我”。
示例：She is strange to me.
误 她不认识我。
正 我不认识她。

strange表示“奇怪的，奇特的”，通常带有贬义。若要表示“独特的”可以用unusual。
示例：我喜欢那幅画，它非常独特。
误 I like that painting, it is very strange.
正 I like that painting, it is very unusual.

在It is strange that...句式中，其中由that引导的主语从句可用陈述语气，也可以用虚拟语气，其区别是：用虚拟语气（should+动词原形）主要强调惊讶之意，其感情色彩比较浓；若不特别强调感情色彩，则用陈述语气。
示例：(1) It’s strange that there are no lights on. 
真奇怪，没有一盏灯是开着的。
(2) It’s strange that there should be no lights on. 
真奇怪，竟然没有一盏灯是开着的。
